source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Для храбрости Женя выкупалась и тихонько пошла отыскивать свою дачу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Плакать Женя и сама умела.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А это еще хуже.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга рассердится или, чего доброго, заплачет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга не поймет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Скверно! Был бы папа, он бы понял.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Каким-то путем она очутилась на берегу речки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Упало на пепельницу настольное зеркало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дым заволок окна.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Грохот ударил по комнате.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она до отказа стянула брови, сжала губы и, целясь в зеркало, надавила курок.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это будет еще лучше.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот так.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В левую руку можно взять револьвер.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Можно было бы соврать, что когда-то отец брал ее с собой на фронт.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хорошо бы так сняться и потом притащить в школу карточку!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вид получился суровый, грозный.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут же у стола в облупленных и исцарапанных ножнах стояла кривая турецкая сабля.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Справа, возле кожаных автомобильных краг, лежал старый, ободранный револьвер.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здесь стоял письменный стол, на нем чернильный прибор, пепельница, небольшое зеркало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она заглянула в соседнюю комнату.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Надо бы повидать и поблагодарить этого человека.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тимур? Кто такой Тимур?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ниже стояла подпись: «Тимур».

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: «Девочка, когда будешь уходить, захлопни крепче дверь».

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Значит, сюда ночью кто-то приходил!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Собаки на полу не было.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Где-то пилили дрова, но здесь, на даче, было по-прежнему тихо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Неподалеку скрипело колодезное колесо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: За окном шумела пышная, омытая дождем листва.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она проснулась только утром.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Наконец она крепко уснула.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Положив голову на жесткий валик дивана, Женя тихонько заплакала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И только здесь, около серой дачи, все было глухо и тихо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Где-то играли на гитаре.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Надо было дожидаться хозяев.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя положила ключ и телеграмму на край стола.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Дура!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да! – Она показала собаке язык.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ты лови разбойников и шпионов, а я… человек.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Очень странно, – чуть не плача, заговорила она.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ну вот! Ты лежишь? И лежи… Очень хорошая собачка… такая с виду умная, симпатичная.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А Женя, потихоньку подвигаясь к распахнутому окну, продолжала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Собака молчала и не шевелилась.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тебе понятно?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Мой папа – командир.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это телеграмма папе.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это вот ключ от нашей квартиры.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Я не вор! Я у вас ничего не взяла.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: – Ты, глупая! – испуганно растопыривая пальцы, закричала Женя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она внимательно оглядела оторопевшую девчонку и, тихо зарычав, легла поперек пути у двери.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Хозяев дома не было.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она постояла, подумала, открыла дверь и через коридор прошла в комнату.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ей не ответили.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она открыла калитку чьей-то серой двухэтажной дачи и по тропинке прошла к крыльцу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Женя огляделась: уже смеркалось, а людей вокруг видно не было.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Скажи, дорогая, пожалуйста, – закричала ей Женя, – как мне пройти отсюда на почту?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Невдалеке она увидела маленькую проворную девчонку, которая с ругательствами волокла за рога упрямую козу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Они помчались за ним вдогонку, громко спрашивая, нет ли у него спичек.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это был местный житель, доктор Ф. Г. Колокольчиков.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он подобрал себе компанию, и они, кажется, гнут против нас дело.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тимку бы поймать, излупить надо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это Тимки Гараева дядя.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Здешний, – нехотя ответил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Это еще что за пропагандист выискался? Здешний?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Когда они отошли, то второй мальчишка сунул замусоленную папиросу за ухо и небрежно спросил.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Не так ли?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вас зовут Михаил Квакин.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Молодой человек, – зажигая спичку и озаряя лицо старшего, сказал Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут же к нему подошли два молодцеватых подростка и, дожидаясь огня, вынули свои папиросы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Георгий вынул портсигар.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Перрон опустел.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ваша сестра приедет рано утром.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да вы зря не беспокойтесь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Восемнадцать куда как лучше!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Сорок не надо! – решительно отказался Георгий.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А то ей тринадцать, мне – восемнадцать, и поэтому она меня совсем не слушается.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, если бы еще мне было лет сорок или хотя бы тридцать.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: С этой негодной девчонкой хлебнешь горя! – огорченно воскликнула Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Поджидая Женю, они пропустили уже два поезда, наконец прошел и третий, последний.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ольга была сердита на Женю и поэтому со своим спутником по дороге говорила мало.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Однако постойте, зачем же вы открываете калитку? Вы можете подождать меня и у забора.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Помните, я никого не боюсь, но я еще не знаю здешних улиц.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Уже темно, поздно, а ее все нет и нет.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я жду младшую сестренку.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Проводите меня до вокзала.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Послушайте, – неожиданно просто предложила ему Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Нет, – ответил человек.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы кто? Артист?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Погодите! – спускаясь со ступени, остановила его она.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Человек был послушен.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Он наклонил голову и вежливо ей ответил.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Из-за куста вышел человек в обыкновенном белом костюме.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Но вот калитка. И будьте добры проникнуть через нее обратно на улицу.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Понятно! – усмехнулась Ольга.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Там, в углу забора, выломаны доски, и я с улицы проник через это отверстие.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Извините, я не кошка.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я?.. Через забор?.. – обиделся человек.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы же для чего-то перелезли через забор.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да, но вы могли стоять и слушать с улицы.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И вот я стоял и слушал.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я не хотел вам мешать.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я сам немного артист.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я не прячусь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Аркадий Гайдар.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Послушайте! Зачем вы прячетесь и что вам здесь надо?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Закончив играть, она быстро поднялась и, повернувшись к кусту, громко спросила:

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: который рос во дворе у забора.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: несколько раз бросала она короткие настороженные взгляды в сторону темного куста,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Еще в то время, когда Ольга напевала эту песенку,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Я не знаю, скоро ли, Только возвращайтесь… хоть когда-нибудь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вы когда вернетесь?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот и улетели в дальний путь.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Да! Летчики-пилоты! Бомбы-пулеметы!

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Как вас ожидала я до утренней зари

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А вы и не поймете на быстром самолете,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ах, если б только раз и два, и три

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ах, если б только раз мне вас еще увидеть,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: перекинула ремень через плечо и стала подбирать музыку к словам недавно услышанной ею песенки.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Она положила аккордеон на колени,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: подарок отца, который он прислал ей ко дню рождения.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Тут из кожаного футляра бережно достала она белый, сверкающий перламутром аккордеон

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: В сумерки, когда уборка была закончена, Ольга вышла на крыльцо.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Вот и все.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: так ее шагов на двадцать к воротам подкатили.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: дубовая, вдвоем не своротишь,

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кадка у меня во дворе стояла

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А что был за народ, что за люди – дело темное.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Пошмыгали, пошмыгали и ушли.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Однако бог миловал – ничего не украли.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Кирпичом по голове стукни – вот я и готова.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, думаю, человек я теперь одинокий, заступиться некому… А много ли мне, старой, надо?

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: А ночью просыпаюсь, и чудится мне, что по двору шныряет кто-то, шмыгает.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Ну, к вечеру, как положено, взгрустнулось, всплакнула.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И пошел и засвистел, милый.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: Прощай, – говорит, – мама.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
sentence: И как пошел, вина не пил.

source: Timur and His Squad (1940) by Arkady Gaidar. In public domain since 2016 according to wikimedia report.
